name: paul harrison
text:
A wonderful bowl of ox tail soup with rice is to be had here for $18.50.

The broth had a lot of flavour and the kitchen was happy to cater to my request for it to be served piping hot.

The meat was tender and slipped off the two massive knuckles easily. It was a generous serve with other mini knuckles and potatoes and carrots.

The accompanying red sambal was delightfully spicy.

I would definitely make the 45 minutes bus ride from the CBD again to try some of the many dishes in the Bain Marie or maybe the Soto Betawi.

Warm service.
